# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SocialSphere .gitignore
# Staged Commit Strategy: Remove future-day entries
# one by one as you complete each day's work
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Core ignores ──────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
.next/
dist/
build/
out/

# ── Environment ───────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env*.local

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
logs/

# ── Uploads ───────────────────────────────────────────
uploads/temp/
public/uploads/

# ── Testing / Coverage ────────────────────────────────
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# ── OS / Editor ───────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/settings.json

# ── TypeScript ────────────────────────────────────────
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Prisma ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Don't ignore schema — only migrations if not ready
# prisma/migrations/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STAGED COMMIT STRATEGY
# Remove each line below when you start that day's work
# This prevents future days from being accidentally committed
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# day-2-auth/*          ← Remove on Day 2
# day-3-profile/*       ← Remove on Day 3
# day-4-posts/*         ← Remove on Day 4
# day-5-comments-likes/* ← Remove on Day 5
# day-6-friends/*       ← Remove on Day 6
# day-7-realtime/*      ← Remove on Day 7
# day-8-notifications/* ← Remove on Day 8
# day-9-privacy/*       ← Remove on Day 9
# day-10-final-polish/* ← Remove on Day 10

# Strategy:
# Before each day's first commit, remove that day's
# line from this file, then stage and commit that
# .gitignore change as the first commit of the day.
# This creates a realistic, honest commit history.
